section.def:
sealed
                (蓋章) means sealed with the seal of the
            court;

paragraph.content:
applications to annul a bankruptcy order;
                (L.N. 77 of
                    1998)

applications to set aside or avoid any settlement, conveyance, transfer,
                security or payment, or to declare for or against the title of the trustee to any
                property adversely claimed;

the Registrar may under the general or special directions of a judge hear and
                determine any application or matter which under the Ordinance and rules may be heard
                and determined in chambers;

to be a transcript of the notes taken by a shorthand writer appointed under
                    subrule (1) or by a shorthand writer attached to the Official Receiver’s Office;
                        and (L.N. 150 of 2014)

to answer interrogatories (if so,
                                                  particulars are to be given of the matters in
                                                  respect of which answers are required);

subsection.def:
information (資訊、資料) includes data,
                text, images, sound codes, computer programmes, software and databases, and any
                combination of them;

paragraph.continued:
and, where any such circumstances are present, whether, and if so how, it
                    is proposed under the voluntary arrangement to make provision for wholly or
                    partly indemnifying the insolvent estate in respect of such claims;

subsection.leadIn:
All the members of the committee must be creditors of the bankrupt;
                                and any creditor (other than one who is fully secured) may be a
                                member, so long as—

subparagraph.content:
the trustee serves the lessor with notice of his intention to disclaim, and the
            lessor does not within 7 days after the receipt of such notice give notice to the
            trustee requiring the matter to be brought before the court;

paragraph.content:
a provisional trustee is appointed under section 12(1A) of the
                    Ordinance, the Official Receiver shall account to the provisional trustee;
